Strong mobilization in Copenhagen and around the world for the climate
Tens of thousands of people demonstrated on Saturday to demand an ambitious and binding agreement on the fight against global warming, around the world and in Copenhagen, where the police made several hundred arrests.
At least thirty thousand people, according to the police, a hundred thousand according to the organizers, marched in the cold in the Danish capital, on the sidelines of the United Nations Climate Conference, responsible for leading by Friday to a agreement which may enter into force on 1 January 2013.
For Connie Hedegaard, Danish president of the climate conference, the growing mobilization on the climate around the world, illustrated by these demonstrations, contributed to making &quot;the political price&quot; of a failure in Copenhagen very high.
