Turkish justice dissolves pro-Kurdish party, decision with serious consequences
Turkey&#39;s Constitutional Court on Friday pronounced the dissolution of the country&#39;s main pro-Kurdish party, a decision that was immediately followed by angry demonstrations in the Kurdish community, in the south-east of the country and in Istanbul.
This decision risks greatly complicating the task of the government, which has just reached out to the Kurdish community in an attempt to end 25 years of conflict.
The Party for a Democratic Society (DTP) was dissolved because it had become a &quot;hotbed of activities detrimental to the independence of the state and its indivisible unity&quot;, court president Hasim Kiliç told the press. , after four days of deliberations.
