This is why the FES service starts at 3 a.m. &quot;so that the roads are clear when the daily commuter traffic begins&quot;.
Where it becomes more difficult is when the snow starts to fall at 7:30 am.
This poses problems, the manager of the road clearing and sanding service tells us &quot;because no motorist is willing to let the salting vehicles pass&quot;.
Then, if it is no longer snowing, we take care of the access roads and feeder roads - such as the Rat-Beil-Straße.
Secondary roads and side streets come last.
Mr. Brauburger is well aware that this always causes some complaints.
