Their participation in the Champions League has brought Real Madrid and Barça 476.4 million since its inception
The Champions League has become a source of revenue for clubs since its birth in 1992.
Indeed, Real Madrid and FC Barcelona won 467.4 million, which places them in third and fifth position among the clubs that have pocketed the most money in this competition.
Manchester United top the list.
Manchester United top the list.
Winning the UEFA Champions League doesn&#39;t just bring glory. It is also one of the main sources of income for big clubs.
Indeed, the competition has distributed 5,362.5 million euros to the 105 teams (including 12 Spanish) who have participated in the event since the tournament was created, during the 1992-1993 season, according to information from the &#39;.
Real Madrid and FC Barcelona were well served during this distribution.
The white club was the third on the continent to receive the most money for its participation, and the only one, with AC Milan, to have won the trophy three times.
The Catalan club, current defending champion and last winner of the old European Cup in 1992, is fifth on the list.
At the top of the list are Manchester United and Bayern Munich, the two teams that, moreover, charged the most money for their participation in the last Champions League.
And that, despite losing to Barça.
On the other hand, Spain is only the third country, when it comes to the money brought in by the Champions League, although it has won more titles than any other (five, while the Italy won four, England three and Germany two).
Distribution
This apparent paradox is explained by the complex procedure for distributing the money applied by UEFA.
For this year, the organization chaired by Michel Platini plans to earn 1,090 million thanks to the Champions League.
Of this sum, UEFA will devote 413.1 million to fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs which took part in the classification matches (including Atlético de Madrid) received 2.1 million.
In addition, those who managed to participate received 3.8 million just for being there, in addition to 550,000 euros for each match played.
There is also a bonus in case of victory (800,000 euros) and equality (400,000 for each team). Those who reach the round of 16 receive three million each, the eight teams who reach the quarter-finals receive 3.3 million.
The last four teams will each receive 4 million.
And the champion will earn 9 million, against the 5.2 received by the other finalist.
Thus, under fixed payments, a club will earn at least 7.1 million, and at most 31.2 million.
On the other hand, Barca pocketed 2.5 million for winning the European Super Cup in August.
But in addition, there are the variable payments, to which 337.8 million are devoted.
This money is distributed according to the proportional value of each television market.
The Spanish market is one of the largest, and has four designated places.
The previous year&#39;s champion gets 40% of the allocated money, 30% for the second, 20% for the third and 10% for the fourth.
The other part will be paid according to the number of matches played during the current year&#39;s edition.
